article.headline: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 69, South Florida 63
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Josh Washington had 21 points as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi defeated South Florida 69-63 on Monday. Both teams played evenly until midway in the second half, when the Islanders (5-3) ran a 9-2 run and took the lead for good. The Bulls (7-2) pulled to within four in the final minute, but couldn't catch up. Solomon Bozeman led the Bulls with 15 points, while Melvin Buckley added 14. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi went 6-for-13 from the 3-point line, while South Florida shot 4-for-17 from beyond the arc. Washington, who had five 3-pointers in nine attempts, left the game with an injury with 2:15 left in the game. The Islanders Chris Daniels led both teams with 11 rebounds. South Florida's Kentrell Gransberry had 10 boards. It was the second time the two teams met. The Islanders also won the first game in 2005.
